Oh come on, it's not that ridiculous to have a map only 4 levels deep. (Though I'll admit the code there is a patch-job over a much worse design that will all be refactored one day...) It's just ridiculous to express in Java. JavaScript's pretty much built on the idea of nested objects/maps.<p><pre><code>    new Ext.Panel({
        width: 400,
        height: 400,
        title: 'Pie Chart with Legend - Favorite Season',
        renderTo: 'container',
        items: {
            store: store,
            xtype: 'piechart',
            dataField: 'total',
            categoryField: 'season',
            //extra styles get applied to the chart defaults
            extraStyle:
            {
                legend:
                {
                    display: 'bottom',
                    padding: 5,
                    font:
                    {
                        family: 'Tahoma',
                        size: 13
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    });</code></pre>
